<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>WithHer - Health Tips</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.0/font/bootstrap-icons.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { background: #fff5f8; font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; }
        .navbar { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff6b9d, #c44569); }
        .navbar-brand, .nav-link { color: white !important; }
        .page-header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff6b9d, #c44569);
            color: white;
            padding: 30px 20px;
            border-radius: 0 0 30px 30px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .tip-of-day {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff6b9d, #c44569);
            color: white;
            border-radius: 20px;
            padding: 25px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .tip-of-day h5 { font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 10px; }
        .tip-of-day p { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; margin: 0; }
        .tip-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 15px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 3px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
            border-left: 4px solid #ff6b9d;
        }
        .tip-card .tip-icon { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .tip-card h6 { color: #333; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 5px; }
        .tip-card p { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; }
        .category-title {
            color: #c44569;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin: 20px 0 10px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }
        .share-btn {
            background: none;
            border: 2px solid #ffccd5;
            color: #ff6b9d;
            border-radius: 20px;
            padding: 4px 12px;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            margin-top: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        .share-btn:hover { background: #fff0f5; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg">
        <div class="container">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="/dashboard">WithHer 💗</a>
            <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
                <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/dashboard"><i class="bi bi-house"></i> Home</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/logout"><i class="bi bi-box-arrow-right"></i> Logout</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="page-header">
        <h3> Daily Health Tips</h3>
        <p>Small steps. Big difference. Every day.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="container mt-4 pb-5">

        <div class="tip-of-day">
            <h5> TIP OF THE DAY</h5>
            <p id="tipOfDay"></p>
        </div>

        <div class="category-title">Period Health</div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Track Your Cycle</h6>
            <p>Mark the first day of your period every month. Changes in your cycle are your body's way of communicating. A calendar or phone note is enough.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Track your period every month. Changes in your cycle are your body talking to you. 💗 WithHer')">Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Drink More Water During Your Period</h6>
            <p>Staying hydrated reduces bloating, eases cramps, and helps your body flush out toxins. Aim for at least 8 glasses of water a day — more during your period.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Drinking water during your period reduces cramps and bloating. Stay hydrated! 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Heat Helps Period Cramps</h6>
            <p>A warm water bottle or warm cloth on your lower abdomen can ease period cramps naturally. It relaxes the muscles and improves blood flow.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('A warm cloth on your lower abdomen can ease period cramps naturally. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="category-title">Know Your Warning Signs</div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>7 Days is the Limit</h6>
            <p>A normal period lasts 2 to 7 days. If you are still bleeding after 7 days — do not ignore it. Visit a clinic. It could be a sign of fibroids, infection, or hormonal imbalance.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Bleeding for more than 7 days is not normal. Please see a doctor. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>One-Sided Pain is a Red Flag</h6>
            <p>Sharp pain on one side of your lower abdomen — especially with a missed period — could be an ectopic pregnancy. This is an emergency. Go to hospital immediately.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Sharp one-sided lower abdominal pain with a missed period needs urgent medical attention.  WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Fever With Pelvic Pain = See a Doctor</h6>
            <p>If you have pelvic pain AND fever, this could be Pelvic Inflammatory Disease (PID). PID can cause infertility if left untreated. Seek medical attention the same day.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Pelvic pain with fever could be PID. See a doctor the same day. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="category-title">Nutrition Tips</div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Eat Iron-Rich Foods</h6>
            <p>Heavy periods can cause iron deficiency. Eat iron-rich foods like sukuma wiki, spinach, beans, meat, and fish. Pair with vitamin C (oranges, tomatoes) to help iron absorption.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Eat sukuma wiki, beans and meat to replenish iron lost during heavy periods. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Reduce Sugar During Your Period</h6>
            <p>High sugar intake worsens period cramps, mood swings, and bloating. Try reducing sodas, sweets, and processed foods during your period week.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Reducing sugar during your period can ease cramps and mood swings. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="category-title"> Mental Wellness</div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Talk About It</h6>
            <p>Many women suffer in silence because they are ashamed or afraid. Talking to a trusted friend, family member, or healthcare provider can make a huge difference. You are not alone.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('You do not have to suffer in silence. Talk to someone you trust. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Walk 30 Minutes a Day</h6>
            <p>Regular light exercise like walking reduces period pain, improves mood, balances hormones, and supports overall reproductive health. You don't need a gym — just walk.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('A 30-minute walk daily improves your mood, reduces period pain and balances hormones. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="category-title">🇰🇪 Vidokezo kwa Kiswahili</div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Jitunze Kila Siku</h6>
            <p>Afya yako ya uzazi ni muhimu. Kula vizuri, kunywa maji, lala vizuri, na tembelea kliniki mara kwa mara. Usisahau — mwili wako unakuambia ukweli. Sikiliza.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Afya yako ya uzazi ni muhimu. Jitunze kila siku. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card">
            <h6>Hospitali Si Adui</h6>
            <p>Wengi wetu tunaogopa kwenda hospitali. Lakini kugundua tatizo mapema kunaweza kuokoa maisha yako. Hospitali za serikali zinatoa huduma za uzazi kwa bei nafuu. Usiogope kutafuta msaada.</p>
            <button class="share-btn" onclick="shareTip('Hospitali si adui. Kutafuta msaada mapema kunaweza kuokoa maisha yako. 💗 WithHer')"> Share</button>
        </div>

    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script>
        const dailyTips = [
            "Track your period every month — changes in your cycle are your body talking to you ",
            "If you have been bleeding for more than 7 days — please see a doctor today ",
            "Drink at least 8 glasses of water daily — your body needs it especially during your period ",
            "Sharp one-sided lower abdominal pain with a missed period is an emergency — go to hospital immediately ",
            "You are not alone. WithHer is here with you every step of the way ",
            "Eat sukuma wiki and beans this week — your body needs iron after your period ",
            "A 30-minute walk today will improve your mood and reduce period pain ",
            "Fever with pelvic pain = see a doctor the same day. Do not wait ",
            "Your health matters. You matter. Never be afraid to seek help ",
            "Painful periods are NOT always normal. If pain stops your daily activities — see a doctor",
            "Regular clinic visits catch problems early. Book a check-up this month ",
            "Talk to someone you trust about your health. Silence can be dangerous ",
            "Reduce sugar this week and notice how your body feels ",
            "Afya yako ni hazina yako. Itunze vizuri kila siku 🇰🇪",
            "HPV vaccine protects against cervical cancer. Ask about it at your nearest clinic "
        ];

        const dayOfYear = Math.floor((new Date() - new Date(new Date().getFullYear(), 0, 0)) / 86400000);
        document.getElementById('tipOfDay').textContent = dailyTips[dayOfYear % dailyTips.length];

        function shareTip(text) {
            if (navigator.share) {
                navigator.share({ text: text });
            } else {
                navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
                alert('Tip copied! Share it with someone who needs it 💗');
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>